{| class= "wikitable" |- |+Class II: Verbs in t-al, "endowed with" ('kux', to live) !colspan=2| Phase ! Example |-align=center !colspan=2|Present | tin (tan-in) kux-t-al "I am living" |-align=center !colspan=2|Past | kux-t-al-ah-en or kux-l-ah-en "I lived" |-align=center !rowspan=2|Future !Simple | hēn (he-in) kux-t-al-e "I shall be living" |-align=center !Going-to future | bin kux-tal-ăk-en "I am going to live" |-align=center |-align=center !colspan=2|Imperative | kux-t-en or kux-t-al-en "Live!" |}
